race.comment: Big field but lots of these are struggling to find form. SACRED FORT (5) has been going well though with a solid run in far tougher two back then finishing runner-up latest in this class after being slowly away. Suited here and looks hard to hold out. SYMPHONITE (9) looks a big threat. Won the maiden with ease two back then runner-up latest here in slightly tougher grade. At top and looks hard to beat. SIMPLY SASSY (11) scored her maiden success last time out over 1400m at Hamilton when stalked the pace and shot away. Farley back aboard and on home track can measure up again.  DOUGAL MCKEEN (8) was placed two back then finished ninth over 1500m at Mornington, beaten 7 lengths. Tends to mix form but trip suits, change of rider and drawn well. Has the ability and is worth including.
